{
  "stem": "12462.5",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "His sentence was a life sentence, one of three defendants who got a life sentence.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And [CLEARS THROAT] he's the only one that completely served off his sentence, of those that received life sentences.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The others got commutations.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, Hess died some time ago.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He-- apparently his mind deteriorated, and he finally committed suicide.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But this was after he was very ill and in Spandau Prison, where he was incarcerated for, I don't know how many years, but a good 30, something like that.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because he was the only defendant left after Speer and von Schirach were dismissed from prison 20 years after the trial.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That'd be in be 19-- [MUMBLES] 1965.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I didn't quite state that.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Several of the defendants-- and these came to be known in some circles as the Speer group-- but they included von Papen and Schacht.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Schacht certainly made a lot of statements that were against the Nazis in his testimony.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And of course, he had said he was willing to plea bargain.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He'd lost all influence in Germany before the war.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And if he'd just retired to his [CLEARS THROAT] country estate and stayed there and not appeared a time or two at public gatherings with Hitler, why, it's very likely he wouldn't even have been indicted.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He felt he had to do that, he said, in order to not be persecuted further, because he was-- had fallen out of favor with the regime.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And he had actually resigned as president of the Reichsbank and been replaced as Reich Minister of Economics before the war began.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So the case against him was on a much weaker basis than the case against those who had been close to Hitler and who had stayed in the Nazi regime during the war.",
      "word_count": 33
    }
  ],
